race.comment: Even race where PURSUANT (6) gets his chance. Showed ability in his first campaign and turned in a nice run fresh when a close-up fourth. Strips much fitter and this is easier. Extra trip a plus and off the low draw should be winding up strongly. SUNSET ROYALE (12) was safely held on debut then improved nicely at second outing. Has upside and extra ground is a plus. Heading the right way. CALIFORNIA FLYER (7) was well off her best before a spell. Resuming in easier grade and looks set for a good return in this company.  BURLEIGH (4) is finding it hard to break through but has solid figures for this.
